member? Yeah, I think it has somewhat. I think 
there's been an increased recognition of the role

41:39.877 --> 41:49.026
that the engineering experiment station could 
play in the development of the state. It wasn't so

41:49.327 --> 41:55.333
apparent in the 70s because we were just moving 
